gate: OPEN
task: S75-TD1
title: Fix S74 Carry-Over Bugs (TD3, TD4, TD5, TD6)
description: |
  Four bugs from S74 were planned but not resolved. Fix all four in this task.

  BUG 1 — S74-TD3: History Date Padding
    Symptom: date strings in HistoryTab display without zero-padding
    (e.g. "1.3.2026" instead of "01.03.2026").
    Location: src/components/screens/object-details/history/
    Fix: ensure date formatting uses padStart(2,'0') or a date-utils formatter
    for day and month fields. Check all date/time rendering in HistoryTab cells.

  BUG 2 — S74-TD4: Map Arrow Stroke Outline
    Symptom: vehicle arrow icons on the map have an unwanted dark stroke/outline
    that looks wrong at small sizes or on certain tile backgrounds.
    Location: src/features/map/ClusterMap.tsx (or vehicle marker icon definition).
    Fix: find SVG/icon definition for the vehicle arrow, remove or adjust the
    stroke attribute. If using DivIcon with SVG, target the stroke style.

  BUG 3 — S74-TD5: Time Popup Behavior
    Symptom: the time range popup (date-range-picker used in TrackingScreen or
    HistoryTab) stays open or re-opens unexpectedly after a track is selected /
    confirmed.
    Location: likely src/components/date-range-picker/ or TrackingScreen.tsx.
    Fix: ensure the popup is closed when the user selects a track or confirms
    the date range. Verify the dismiss/close callback is called at the right time.

  BUG 4 — S74-TD6: Track Selection Hang
    Symptom: after selecting a vehicle and date range in TrackingScreen and pressing
    "Build track", the UI hangs or shows a perpetual loader without resolving.
    Location: TrackingScreen.tsx → TrackingActionScreen.tsx, hook useTrackData or
    equivalent.
    Root cause candidates:
      a) Promise not resolving due to missing await or unhandled rejection
      b) Loading state not reset on error (setLoading(false) missing in catch)
      c) Race condition between vehicle select and date range state
    Fix: inspect the track request flow, ensure loading state is always cleared
    in both success and error paths, and add error display to the user.

acceptance:
  - History dates display with zero-padded day and month (01.03.2026)
  - Vehicle arrows on map have no unwanted stroke outline
  - Time picker popup closes after user confirms date selection
  - Building a track never hangs indefinitely — either succeeds or shows error

requires: [FRONTEND_DEV]
estimated: 3 hours
